# correlation between the continuous variables the the 
numeric_vars <- sapply(churnTrain, is.numeric)
corrs <- cor(churnTrain[numeric_vars])
corrplot(corrs, method = "number", tl.cex = 0.75)

Finding a perfect colinearity between the of four pairs of total charge and total minutes variables is of course no surprise, phone charges are not random variables! However it is somewhat surprising that there is no linear relation between any other pairs of variables. A scatterplot matrix of a subset of the continuous variables reveals the extent of any pairwise relationship and how certain variables contain large amounts of zeros.
